OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F465A1777551071
OL,3,CFormer police officer barred for using
OL,4,Cracist and sexist language while on
OL,5,Cduty
OL,7,FA former Gwent Police officer would
OL,8,Fhave been sacked without notice, had
OL,9,Fhe not already resigned, over
OL,10,Fsexualised and discriminatory language
OL,11,Fhe used whilst on duty.
OL,13,FA misconduct hearing on Tuesday, 28
OL,14,FApril heard how former Police
OL,15,FConstable (PC) Wayne Tancock made
OL,16,Fsexualised comments about women and
OL,17,Fdiscriminatory language against the
OL,18,Ftraveller community, while in a police
OL,19,Fcar on duty.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/5
